4. distinct()
      Concept
          
          distinct() is an intermediate operation used to remove duplicate elements from a Stream. It returns a Stream containing only unique elements.
          
          Syntax:
          
          stream.distinct()



1. Remove duplicate numbers from a list.
      Program
          import java.util.Arrays;
          import java.util.List;
          
          public class DistinctNumbers {
              public static void main(String[] args) {
          
                  List<Integer> numbers = Arrays.asList(
                          10, 20, 30, 20, 40, 10, 50, 30);
          
                  numbers.stream()
                          .distinct()
                          .forEach(System.out::println);
              }
          }
          Output
          10
          20
          30
          40
          50



2. Given a list of strings, print only unique strings.
Program
import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.List;

public class DistinctStrings {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        List<String> names = Arrays.asList(
                "Java", "Python", "Java",
                "Spring", "Python", "React");

        names.stream()
                .distinct()
                .forEach(System.out::println);
    }
}
Output
Java
Python
Spring
React






3. From a list of employees, print unique department names.
    Program
        import java.util.Arrays;
        import java.util.List;
        
        class Employee {
        
            int id;
            String name;
            String department;
        
            Employee(int id, String name, String department) {
                this.id = id;
                this.name = name;
                this.department = department;
            }
        }
        
        public class UniqueDepartments {
            public static void main(String[] args) {
        
                List<Employee> employees = Arrays.asList(
                        new Employee(101, "Ravi", "IT"),
                        new Employee(102, "Anil", "HR"),
                        new Employee(103, "Priya", "IT"),
                        new Employee(104, "Kiran", "Finance"),
                        new Employee(105, "Rahul", "HR")
                );
        
                employees.stream()
                        .map(emp -> emp.department)
                        .distinct()
                        .forEach(System.out::println);
            }
        }
        Output
            IT
            HR
            Finance
        
        Note: First, map() extracts the department from each Employee object. Then distinct() removes duplicate department names.




Summary :
| Question                 | Stream Methods Used    | Purpose                                    |
| ------------------------ | ---------------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| Remove duplicate numbers | `distinct()`           | Removes duplicate integers                 |
| Print unique strings     | `distinct()`           | Removes duplicate strings                  |
| Print unique departments | `map()` + `distinct()` | Extracts and removes duplicate departments |




